cs.LG, cs.IT, cs.DS, cs.AI, cs.SI 

The paper deals with generalization bounds for classifiers learned from non-IID data, which is a common topic in machine learning (cs.LG). The use of graph fractional covers to decompose the dependency graph is a technique from information theory (cs.IT) and graph theory (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the application of the bounds to ranking statistics (cs.AI) and stationary mixing processes (cs.SI).
